# Tailwind CSS Best Practices

## Core Principles
- Utility classes over custom CSS
- @apply sparingly (only for repeated patterns)
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Use shadcn/ui components when available
- Consistent spacing scale (2, 4, 6, 8)

## Layout Patterns
- Flexbox: `flex flex-col gap-4` (not manual margins)
- Grid: `grid grid-cols-3 gap-4`
- Container: `container mx-auto px-4 max-w-6xl`

## Responsive
- Mobile-first: base styles, then `md:`, `lg:`
- Breakpoints: sm (640px), md (768px), lg (1024px), xl (1280px)
- Hide/show: `hidden md:block`

## Colors & Typography
- Semantic naming: `bg-primary`, `text-secondary`
- Proper contrast for accessibility
- Type scale: `text-sm/base/lg/xl`
- Line height: `leading-tight/normal/relaxed`

## State Variants
- `hover:bg-gray-100`
- `focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500`
- `disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed`
- `dark:bg-gray-800` (when dark mode enabled)

## Common Patterns
```tsx
// Button
className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-600 disabled:opacity-50"

// Card
className="bg-white rounded-lg shadow p-6"

// Input
className="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500"

// Centered content
className="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-6xl"

// Flex with gap
className="flex items-center gap-4"

// Responsive grid
className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6"
```